An FCT High Court has sentenced a former member of the House of Representatives and chairman of the Adhoc Committee on Petroleum Subsidy, Hon. Farouk Lawan, to seven years imprisonment. Lawan was accused of demanding $3 million bribe from billionaire businessman, Femi Otedola, in order to remove his firms from the list of companies indicted for oil subsidy fraud by the House Committee. Lawan represented Kiru/Bebeji federal constituency of Kano State in the House of Representatives from 1999 to 2015. Details Laterâ€¦